 The first task on SQLZoo is brushing up on the basics of the select statement which includes the usage of the where , from clauses and comparisons.
 
 Q1) Modify it to show the population of Germany
 ---> SELECT population FROM world WHERE name = 'Germany'
 Q2) Show the name and the population for 'Sweden', 'Norway' and 'Denmark'.
 ---> SELECT name , population from world WHERE name IN ('Sweden' , 'Norway' , 'Denmark')
 Q3) Show the country and the area for countries with an area between 200,000 and 250,000.
 ---> SELECT name , area FROM world WHERE area BETWEEN 200000 AND 250000 
                      0R
      SELECT name , area FROM world WHERE area > 200000 AND area < 250000

